ENPH Must read post on the Yahoo board explaining the terms of the new deal Far more complex than I imagined possible but extremely bullish for the longer term Heres an excerpt The way this type of hedge works for a very low cost in this case the 1 per share 65M total The company benefits dollar for dollar actually 644M per 1 increase in share price as the share price rises above 205 all the way to 2523 As share price rises they can exercise this call and with the proceeds reduce the potential net cost andor dilution if any to pay off the CN in 2024 Further it confirms that the company and the purchasers of the warrants expect share price to continue to go up much higher Once share price goes above 2525 60 above current market the benefit of the hedge is capped and owners of the warrants can buy shares from the company for 2525
